AUDIENCE: Really quick
question about farro.

00:44:58.950 --> 00:45:01.680
So the more and more I
shop, I see quick grains,

00:45:01.680 --> 00:45:03.220
so like five-minute farrow.

00:45:03.220 --> 00:45:04.030
HUGH ACHESON: Yep.

00:45:04.030 --> 00:45:05.660
AUDIENCE: My question is
it looks the exact same--

00:45:05.660 --> 00:45:06.368
HUGH ACHESON: Eh.

00:45:06.368 --> 00:45:08.450
AUDIENCE: --but what
do they do to it?

00:45:08.450 --> 00:45:10.494
And are you losing any
nutritional benefit by--

00:45:10.494 --> 00:45:11.410
HUGH ACHESON: You are.

00:45:11.410 --> 00:45:12.410
AUDIENCE: --using a quick grain.

00:45:12.410 --> 00:45:14.076
HUGH ACHESON: Yeah,
it's the same thing.

00:45:14.076 --> 00:45:21.320
It's like, I talk a lot about
the advent of Minute Rice.

00:45:21.320 --> 00:45:25.050
How hard do things have to
be when we minutize them?

00:45:25.050 --> 00:45:28.590
So I mean, farrow cooks
in 15, 20 minutes.

00:45:28.590 --> 00:45:31.120
So if you buy-- basically,
that's pre-cooking it,

00:45:31.120 --> 00:45:34.290
drying it, and then-- so it's
just you're re-hydrating it

00:45:34.290 --> 00:45:35.620
in five minutes.

00:45:35.620 --> 00:45:38.260
So what I want to
do is teach people

00:45:38.260 --> 00:45:41.180
the beauty of cooking
something from raw, the ease

00:45:41.180 --> 00:45:42.900
of cooking something from raw.

00:45:42.900 --> 00:45:45.350
And I want to get
back to a society that

00:45:45.350 --> 00:45:48.630
doesn't feel like spending 10
more minutes in the kitchen

00:45:48.630 --> 00:45:53.680
at the stove is an inconvenient
move or a loss of time.

00:45:53.680 --> 00:45:56.560
It's also going to strip a lot
of nutrients in that process.

00:45:56.560 --> 00:46:00.070
And it's also just going through
so many more hands and machines

00:46:00.070 --> 00:46:02.180
that I just think I can
simplify the process.

00:46:02.180 --> 00:46:06.170
So convenience through
inconvenience from convenience.

00:46:06.170 --> 00:46:08.240
I don't know if that
makes any sense at all.

00:46:08.240 --> 00:46:10.630
But yeah, but yeah.

